blog.description: Ana/28/🇪🇸SWIFTIE❤️/RM⚽️/IG:ana_mz13 / Tw:Ana_mz13/1989 WT 19.06.15 Cologne / Rep Tour 22.06.18 London.❤️ MET TAYLOR 22 JUNE 2018

summary: Taylor has always been my unconditional support, she with her music helped me with anxiety and with to be disappointed with a...
caption: Taylor has always been my unconditional support, she with her music helped me with anxiety and with to be disappointed with a lot of person who had before in my life. She show me that to be different is the best thing that can happen to you in life. I still remember how I feel when I saw her live for the first time, the 19 June of 2015, in Cologne. My family and I traveled from Spain only to see her and for have the chance to meet her, but that time there was no luck, but that trip was the best trip of my life. 2017 was a horrible year for me, anxiety returned to my life because all the stress I suffered to finish my master’s degree, my two grandparents died in less than 1 month….a year to forget, except for the fact to have Reputation in my hands, the last 10 November. Taylor has always been with me in my best and worse times, she is my lifeline, that’s why when I saw that she didn’t come to Spain with Reputation Stadium Tour, I was saving up to travel to other country to see her. This time is London, Wembley, I’m looking forward to the 22 of June and can see you again……  My only wish right now is that I can return from that trip and I could meet you, and to be able to thank you in person for everything you do with your music for me. I need hug you and say thank you. @taylorswift see you in Wembley the 22 of June, my mother, my sister @yoursisnredunderlined and me will be in the Section BK 123, Row 34, Seats 24-26. @taylornation @tree-paine

summary: Sorry I haven’t been active my Mum (who is a massive Taylor fan aswell) married the love of her life on Saturday! It was a...
body: Sorry I haven’t been active my Mum (who is a massive Taylor fan aswell) married the love of her life on Saturday! It was a beautiful ceremony with a perfect party afterwards. As my Mum’s oldest child I was given the honour of giving a speech. As we are both huge TS fans I was really hoping to somehow fit a lyric of Taylor’s into it. The one line out of her whole discography that kept coming to mind was ‘I’m doing better than I ever was.’ That really is how my Mum feels right now. She had such a hard time bringing up my sisters and I, now, she has found the perfect person to enjoy the rest of her life with. When I read that line in my speech stating that my Mum was doing better than she ever was, she burst into tears. Everyone congratulated me on my speech and a lot of people (not knowing it was a TS lyric) commented on that line and how it really hit home. I would like to thank @taylorswift for being one of the reasons me and my mum are so close and how her small role played such a massive part in my Mum’s special day. Ps- she wanted so bad to attend one of the rep tour dates with me but due to the wedding preparations & then honeymoon she couldn’t make any of the Europe dates - she loved watching all my videos though & thought you were ‘fantastic’. Here are some photos in case you somehow see this and would like to look 💘💕
